article.headline: Denver 56, South Alabama 54
article.story: DENVER -- Nate Rohnert scored 12 points and made the game-winning basket with five seconds left to lead the University of Denver to a 56-54 win over South Alabama on Thursday night. Rohnert also tallied two rebounds, two steals and a block in 38 minutes of play. Rob Lewis added 11 points for Denver (9-11, 4-5 Sun Belt Conference), which led 37-28 at halftime. The Jaguars (11-10, 4-6) were paced by Deandre' Coleman with 17 points and nine rebounds. Teammate Brandon Davis added 15 points and seven rebounds. The Pioneers were four points behind with 1:55 left in the game when Nigel Peter-Denman went to the free-throw line for Rohnert, who was bleeding and forced to the bench. Peter-Denman sank both shots. Brian Stafford made a 3-pointer to give Denver a 54-53 lead, but South Alabama's C.J. Garner evened the score by making one of two free throws with 39 seconds remaining. Rohnert made a layup with five seconds left to seal the win.
